1
00:00:15,162 --> 00:00:18,016
=Reply High School=

2
00:00:18,016 --> 00:00:19,104
(Previously) (15 students entering WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL)
TRAINEE: Are we going to be late?

3
00:00:19,578 --> 00:00:20,608
TRAINEE: Is this WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL?

4
00:00:20,608 --> 00:00:21,824
TRAINEE: WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL.

5
00:00:22,112 --> 00:00:23,599
(WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL is divided into classes by era)

6
00:00:23,966 --> 00:00:24,928
(NICHOLAS, KASSHO, JUSTIN)
HYUNJUN: Since this is the 90s,

7
00:00:24,928 --> 00:00:26,848
(HYUNJUN, WOOLIN: Class '90)
HYUNJUN: Ulsan wasn't a metropolitan city back then.

8
00:00:26,848 --> 00:00:27,744
TRAINEE: Really?

9
00:00:27,744 --> 00:00:29,664
HYUNJUN: No, we're in the '90s right now, right?

10
00:00:29,799 --> 00:00:32,064
(HANBI, SONGHA, KACHIN, SADAHARU, TATA: Class '00)
HANBI: It's all-in-one now, so we have to charge it.

11
00:00:32,896 --> 00:00:33,920
HANBI: It's not now.

12
00:00:34,074 --> 00:00:35,118
HANBI: We're talking about it happening in the future.

13
00:00:36,122 --> 00:00:36,736
(DANIEL, HARUTA, HAMIN, CHARLIE, JAEWON: Class '10)

14
00:00:36,736 --> 00:00:37,728
TRAINEE: Wow, I've never seen this before.

15
00:00:39,418 --> 00:00:40,776
JAEWON: Oh, wow!

16
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,392
HANBI: Wow, is the class name finally being announced?

17
00:00:44,032 --> 00:00:45,120
(To the class that achieves excellent scores)
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: The class that obtains)

18
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:46,233
(TEACHERS' OFFICE:
the highest score during school life,)

19
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:49,466
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: will receive a special benefit.)

20
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:53,866
- DANIEL: So that's why they said names are important!
- TRAINEE: Now I see why it's important.

21
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:56,000
(Decided by fan votes)
ALL: One, two, three.

22
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,566
(Names of each class
A.U.I, Five Boys Over Flowers, WONHA~JANNI)

23
00:00:58,720 --> 00:01:01,866
(Unfolding in the hallway after shortened classes)
TRAINEE: The game that will decide your places is

24
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:04,200
(Dormitory spot assignment game, Red Light, Green Light)
DANIEL: Red Light, Green Light.

25
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:05,120
(HAMIN)
TRAINEE: Since everyone's here...

26
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:05,952
(The flower hasn't even bloomed)
TRAINEE: Are we losing?

27
00:01:05,952 --> 00:01:06,786
(WOOLIN, JAEWON)
TRAINEE: Buddy!

28
00:01:07,936 --> 00:01:08,640
TRAINEE: Ha!

29
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:11,866
(Bees moving around, finding their spots)

30
00:01:12,090 --> 00:01:13,722
DANIEL: What, what, what!

31
00:01:13,722 --> 00:01:14,699
DANIEL: Ahhh!

32
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:15,766
(No matter what the seeker says)

33
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:18,912
(Flying away to find a good spot)

34
00:01:19,599 --> 00:01:20,800
DANIEL: What happened?

35
00:01:22,208 --> 00:01:23,136
(Room 201: JUSTIN, HYUNJUN, KASSHO, HARUTA,)
TRAINEE: Hey, but there are a lot of us.

36
00:01:23,418 --> 00:01:24,760
(HAMIN, SADAHARU, JAEWON, WOOLIN)
TRAINEE: Snacks, dumbbells.

37
00:01:25,248 --> 00:01:26,592
TRAINEE: I guess I'll have to wear this to school.

38
00:01:26,592 --> 00:01:28,512
(Room 202: HANBI, SONGHA,
NICHOLAS, DANIEL, KACHIN, CHARLIE, TATA)

39
00:01:28,512 --> 00:01:30,592
(Without realizing time is passing)
TRAINEE: Oh, what do I do?

40
00:01:32,122 --> 00:01:33,888
(After enjoying the first night at the dormitory
without realizing how much time has passed)

41
00:01:33,888 --> 00:01:34,599
TRAINEE: What?

42
00:01:35,162 --> 00:01:36,452
TRAINEE: Did you guys write in your journals?

43
00:01:37,184 --> 00:01:40,233
(The second day at WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL is dawning)

44
00:01:44,299 --> 00:01:46,033
(Echoing through the quiet dormitory)

45
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:49,299
(Somewhere, there's a '90s beat playing)

46
00:01:52,058 --> 00:01:54,560
(The owner of the alarm sound is JUSTIN)

47
00:01:57,733 --> 00:02:01,133
(Quickly finding the phone to turn off the alarm)

48
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:05,440
(Everyone squirms at the sound of the alarm)

49
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:07,488
(Reading the room)

50
00:02:10,906 --> 00:02:13,920
(Front row HYUNJUN also moves)

51
00:02:15,366 --> 00:02:17,366
(Springing up from bed)

52
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:20,736
(Angry pink hair)

53
00:02:21,402 --> 00:02:23,168
(Checking something by the window...)

54
00:02:23,168 --> 00:02:26,466
(WOOJEONG
Two characters carved together with WOOLIN last night)

55
00:02:26,554 --> 00:02:31,648
=Episode 2=
(With You)

56
00:02:32,466 --> 00:02:35,533
(Meanwhile, they are waking up one by one)

57
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:40,700
(KASSHO stares quietly at the bed...)

58
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:46,633
(Diving onto SADAHARU's bed)

59
00:02:47,233 --> 00:02:51,933
(Indoor shoes might be uncomfortable,
but he'll come down soon)

60
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,966
(Waking SADAHARU and running away)

61
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:58,566
(In Room 202, someone is targeting a sleeping friend)

62
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:02,366
SONGHA: DANIEL, you have to wake up.

63
00:03:02,816 --> 00:03:04,734
(And then goes back to sleep himself)

64
00:03:05,146 --> 00:03:07,776
(Assessing the situation...)

65
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:13,133
(No intention of waking up yet)

66
00:03:13,728 --> 00:03:14,649
SONGHA: Wake up!

67
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:18,600
(SONGHA prefers a light breakfast)

68
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,330
(Cereal - It might seem viral
since it appears frequently,)

69
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,033
(but we swear it's not viral marketing.
The kids just like eating it)

70
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:25,666
(Having breakfast while spacing out)

71
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,608
HYUNJUN: Hey, WOOJEONG is really pretty!

72
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,352
(More cereal here too)

73
00:03:33,666 --> 00:03:35,033
(Cereal spoon)

74
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:37,900
(Dig the ground,
see if a single cereal grain comes out...)

75
00:03:38,138 --> 00:03:38,909
(Chicken singing)
TRAINEE: Oh my!

76
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:41,434
HYUNJUN: What's that?

77
00:03:41,966 --> 00:03:42,880
WOOLIN: It's a chicken!

78
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,608
HYUNJUN: Is it a chicken?

79
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,944
WOOLIN: Only people can make a sound like that.

80
00:03:47,706 --> 00:03:48,896
(Ahhh)

81
00:03:50,938 --> 00:03:52,531
(Ahhh)

82
00:03:53,562 --> 00:03:55,904
(Awake)

83
00:03:56,466 --> 00:03:58,554
(Thank you, wake-up fairies)

84
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,384
HYUNJUN: Shouldn't we take the cameras?

85
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:05,600
(Thinking the cameras installed
by the staff in the morning)

86
00:04:05,866 --> 00:04:07,633
(were left on the playground by mistake,)

87
00:04:07,898 --> 00:04:08,832
(he retrieves them)

88
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:09,766
HYUNJUN: It's heavy though.

89
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:12,192
(With a kind heart)
HYUNJUN: Collecting the camera.

90
00:04:13,824 --> 00:04:16,341
(A disappointing result)
TRAINEE: Thank you for filming us so diligently.

91
00:04:17,306 --> 00:04:20,320
(Staff reinstalling the cameras)

92
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,133
(Meanwhile, CHARLIE is still sleeping)

93
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,766
(Hugging TORONG tightly and sleeping soundly)

94
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:32,000
(Waking up immediately at the sound of the alarm)

95
00:04:32,566 --> 00:04:35,400
(Tidying up the bed without delay!)

96
00:04:35,674 --> 00:04:37,056
(Changing clothes)

97
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:40,566
(Open)

98
00:04:40,858 --> 00:04:41,600
(Laughing)

99
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,442
CHARLIE: Watch this.

100
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:46,000
(Starting to dress TORONG in his pajamas)

101
00:04:46,106 --> 00:04:47,776
(Tight fit)

102
00:04:49,266 --> 00:04:51,366
(Meticulously, even the arms)

103
00:04:52,966 --> 00:04:55,633
(Becoming CHARONG (CHARLIE+TORONG)...)

104
00:04:55,834 --> 00:04:56,977
(Photo time)
DANIEL: Feel bunny today?

105
00:04:58,138 --> 00:04:59,520
(Looks fierce)

106
00:04:59,706 --> 00:05:01,728
(Let go, you brat!)

107
00:05:02,554 --> 00:05:03,040
(Slam)

108
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:03,872
CHARLIE: I want it.

109
00:05:04,122 --> 00:05:04,640
DANIEL: Yeah.

110
00:05:04,928 --> 00:05:05,613
(TORONG fainting time)
TRAINEE: Sunscreen.

111
00:05:05,664 --> 00:05:06,688
TRAINEE: Did you eat breakfast?

112
00:05:06,697 --> 00:05:08,266
TRAINEE: Did you take everything?

113
00:05:08,704 --> 00:05:10,016
(Students who finished start heading to school)
TRAINEE: Can I eat this?

114
00:05:10,842 --> 00:05:12,063
- HANBI: Going to school.
- SONGHA: Going to school.

115
00:05:12,338 --> 00:05:13,917
HANBI: School arrival complete.

116
00:05:14,366 --> 00:05:16,576
JUSTIN: School! School! School!

117
00:05:17,946 --> 00:05:18,866
TRAINEE: Bye-bye!

118
00:05:18,866 --> 00:05:19,733
KASSHO: Bye!

119
00:05:19,999 --> 00:05:21,933
(HYUNJUN is also here at the school)

120
00:05:22,042 --> 00:05:24,966
SONGHA: That guy. Dyed it pink
and came to school like that.

121
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,833
(The pink-haired one also arrived at the classroom)

122
00:05:26,906 --> 00:05:28,320
(Empty seat)

123
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:29,499
HAMIN: Why aren't they here yet?

124
00:05:29,722 --> 00:05:30,622
HARUTA: Are they late?

125
00:05:30,816 --> 00:05:31,840
SONGHA: Okay, TATA's late!

126
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:33,984
HANBI: Latecomer.

127
00:05:34,766 --> 00:05:37,099
(JAEWON & TATA
The two latecomers are still in the dormitory)

128
00:05:37,099 --> 00:05:38,016
JAEWON: Shouldn't we get going?

129
00:05:39,034 --> 00:05:39,956
TATA: Ugh?

130
00:05:40,954 --> 00:05:43,040
(First, keep the snacks)

131
00:05:44,346 --> 00:05:46,077
TRAINEE: We have to go, hurry up!

132
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:49,766
(Even though the bell has rung, let's run anyway)

133
00:05:50,330 --> 00:05:51,105
JAEWON: Hello!

134
00:05:51,802 --> 00:05:53,152
(Disciplinary committee catching latecomers)

135
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:54,528
HANBI: Hey, latecomers!

136
00:05:55,499 --> 00:05:56,384
(To latecomers)
HANBI: Time is money.

137
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,744
HANBI: TATA's late! TATA's late!

138
00:05:59,834 --> 00:06:00,256
TATA: Huh?

139
00:06:01,306 --> 00:06:02,117
TRAINEE: I didn't know.

140
00:06:05,626 --> 00:06:06,499
TRAINEE: Latecomer, latecomer.

141
00:06:06,499 --> 00:06:07,840
(All students have arrived, including latecomer TATA)
TRAINEE: You're late, latecomer.

142
00:06:12,066 --> 00:06:14,720
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: Today is Student Record Day.)

143
00:06:15,808 --> 00:06:18,966
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: Students, please receive
the distributed Student Records)

144
00:06:19,466 --> 00:06:22,066
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: and fill out the basic information.)

145
00:06:24,122 --> 00:06:25,504
(Student Record Day)

146
00:06:25,658 --> 00:06:29,568
(Student Records)

147
00:06:29,568 --> 00:06:31,488
(Personal details, physical details, fitness test,
preference test, peer assessment)

148
00:06:31,488 --> 00:06:33,792
(Various tests are planned to be conducted)

149
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,966
HYUNJUN: Doesn't this have an old-fashioned vibe?

150
00:06:36,058 --> 00:06:36,984
KASSHO: Oh!

151
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:38,633
TRAINEE: It's cool though.

152
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:40,133
(JUSTIN)
WOOLIN: You'll be good at this. Flexibility!

153
00:06:40,378 --> 00:06:41,076
(HYUNJUN)
JUSTIN: He's good at it.

154
00:06:41,866 --> 00:06:43,099
(Nods of approval)
HYUNJUN: I'm really good with flexibility.

155
00:06:43,099 --> 00:06:44,224
JUSTIN: This guy's really the best, right?

156
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:45,533
JUSTIN: The best flexibility.

157
00:06:45,566 --> 00:06:46,528
WOOLIN: I think I'll be the worst.

158
00:06:47,130 --> 00:06:49,349
JUSTIN: It's okay, there's still JAEWON.

159
00:06:49,866 --> 00:06:53,999
(Class '10 JAEWON: An unknown rivalry as middle
and high school classmates with WOOLIN)

160
00:06:54,112 --> 00:06:54,720
(This is the chance to find out)
JUSTIN: Who ranks higher?

161
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,120
(who ranks higher between JAEWON and me)
WOOLIN: Between me and JAEWON...

162
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,520
HANBI: Future hope...

163
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:02,699
(Born in '03)
HANBI: This was so difficult back in school.

164
00:07:03,264 --> 00:07:04,864
TATA: Oh! Running is here.

165
00:07:05,599 --> 00:07:08,199
(18 years old, blooming with laughter at just 'Running')
TRAINEE: Hehe, 50m sprint!

166
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:09,699
HANBI: What are you most confident about here, TATA?

167
00:07:09,699 --> 00:07:10,432
(Pointing precisely)

168
00:07:10,432 --> 00:07:10,976
HANBI: Running?

169
00:07:10,976 --> 00:07:11,488
TATA: It's running.

170
00:07:11,488 --> 00:07:12,166
HANBI: 50m sprint?

171
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:13,099
HANBI: Do you run very fast, TATA?

172
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:13,792
(Nods)
TATA: Yes.

173
00:07:13,856 --> 00:07:14,889
(Confident)

174
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,288
TATA: I'm first place at school.

175
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,312
HANBI: You are number one in school?

176
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,166
SONGHA: Hey, HANBI is really fast too!

177
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:21,299
HANBI: Every time I catch the bus...

178
00:07:22,144 --> 00:07:23,008
HANBI: Max speed.

179
00:07:27,066 --> 00:07:29,633
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: The remaining part
of your school records)

180
00:07:29,633 --> 00:07:32,666
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: will be completed
with the PE teacher.)

181
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:33,984
HYUNJUN: The PE teacher?

182
00:07:33,984 --> 00:07:34,601
WOOLIN: Who is it?

183
00:07:36,224 --> 00:07:37,280
(Chaotic)
TRAINEE: A handsome guy.

184
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,016
HAMIN: Oh?

185
00:07:38,619 --> 00:07:39,968
(Quiet...)

186
00:07:40,224 --> 00:07:41,280
HARUTA: Oh, it was sudden!

187
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:44,966
(The secret one-day PE Teacher)
MAX CHANGMIN: I'll be back.

188
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:48,566
(24 years since debut, TVXQ!'S MAX CHANGMIN)

189
00:07:48,566 --> 00:07:51,166
(Group & Solo, Symbol of 2nd Gen Idols)

190
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:54,133
(Active consistently in Korea and Japan)

191
00:07:54,866 --> 00:07:59,533
(And there is a passionate fan of his
among the 15 trainees)

192
00:08:00,999 --> 00:08:03,833
(During the pre-interview)
HARUTA: I've admired TVXQ! for a long time.

193
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:06,199
HARUTA: I've always liked CHANGMIN

194
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:09,466
HARUTA: I went to see him on stage once.

195
00:08:09,466 --> 00:08:11,099
HARUTA: It was so cool.

196
00:08:11,099 --> 00:08:14,233
HARUTA: It made me want to become an idol too.

197
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:18,144
HARUTA: I told him that I liked him, all this time.

198
00:08:18,496 --> 00:08:22,368
HARUTA: He asked to have a meal together, so we did.

199
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:24,233
HARUTA: It was the best!

200
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:27,199
HARUTA: The happiest time of my life.

201
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:30,099
(Offering the second happiest time in his life)

202
00:08:31,066 --> 00:08:33,799
(CHANGMIN is here!)
MAX CHANGMIN: Wow, really!

203
00:08:35,168 --> 00:08:36,352
MAX CHANGMIN: So pretty.

204
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:38,666
(The classroom is on the third floor.
Found the wrong place)

205
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:39,712
MAX CHANGMIN: Is it here...?

206
00:08:41,344 --> 00:08:42,944
MAX CHANGMIN: Where should I go?
Do I need to go up more?

207
00:08:44,178 --> 00:08:45,408
(Excuse me, can I ask for directions?)
MAX CHANGMIN: There, do I need to go up more?

208
00:08:45,408 --> 00:08:46,464
(Flustered)
MAX CHANGMIN: Oh, yes.

209
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:50,066
(Striding confidently unlike before)

210
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,736
(Classroom sign discovered)

211
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:55,766
(Standing in front of Class '10)

212
00:08:55,968 --> 00:08:57,120
MAX CHANGMIN: Ah, I'm nervous.

213
00:08:58,714 --> 00:08:59,424
(Knock knock)

214
00:09:02,299 --> 00:09:04,066
(The teacher's here, guys!)

215
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:06,466
(CHANGMIN)

216
00:09:07,986 --> 00:09:09,280
TRAINEE: Hello!

217
00:09:09,312 --> 00:09:10,432
(Murmuring)

218
00:09:10,799 --> 00:09:12,033
SONGHA: What's going on?

219
00:09:12,787 --> 00:09:13,888
HANBI: Ah, I'm excited, excited!

220
00:09:13,888 --> 00:09:14,496
KACHIN: Ah, it's scary.

221
00:09:15,399 --> 00:09:17,088
(Everyone is flustered with the teacher's arrival)
ALL: Hello!

222
00:09:18,176 --> 00:09:19,166
MAX CHANGMIN: Hi, everyone!

223
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,256
(Surprised eye contact)

224
00:09:20,256 --> 00:09:21,568
TRAINEE: He... hello!

225
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:23,466
MAX CHANGMIN: What's this?
Are you standing up to greet me now?

226
00:09:23,466 --> 00:09:24,064
ALL: Yes!

227
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,333
(Feeling happy, touching the nose)

228
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:28,233
MAX CHANGMIN: What, is there a formal greeting?

229
00:09:28,266 --> 00:09:29,699
(There's nothing like that)
TRAINEE: No, not yet.

230
00:09:29,699 --> 00:09:31,399
MAX CHANGMIN: Okay then, sit comfortably! Let's sit.

231
00:09:33,699 --> 00:09:35,399
(Still bewildered)
MAX CHANGMIN: Then...

232
00:09:35,399 --> 00:09:37,866
MAX CHANGMIN: Let me introduce myself.

233
00:09:37,866 --> 00:09:39,966
MAX CHANGMIN: Today, at WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL,

234
