HARUTA: But...

462
00:16:58,277 --> 00:16:59,872
HARUTA: The phone power was off.

463
00:17:00,288 --> 00:17:01,774
HARUTA: Ring ring ring!

464
00:17:02,112 --> 00:17:02,856
HARUTA: But

465
00:17:02,976 --> 00:17:03,970
HARUTA: the power was off at that time...

466
00:17:04,608 --> 00:17:06,976
(Silence scarier than ghosts)

467
00:17:06,976 --> 00:17:08,256
DANIEL: Scary.

468
00:17:09,376 --> 00:17:09,792
(Rescue delayed friend with a late reaction)

469
00:17:09,792 --> 00:17:11,860
- DANIEL: So scary!
- MAX CHANGMIN: Oh, suddenly scared?

470
00:17:12,672 --> 00:17:14,528
(WONHA~JANNI class, living by helping each other)

471
00:17:14,528 --> 00:17:15,450
(CHARLIE & JAEWON)
MAX CHANGMIN: Are you two okay?

472
00:17:15,450 --> 00:17:15,944
CHARLIE: Yes.

473
00:17:17,024 --> 00:17:19,979
(What's okay?)
MAX CHANGMIN: No, no.

474
00:17:19,979 --> 00:17:21,472
(Getting by with laughter) (Don't know why laughing)
MAX CHANGMIN: It's not the "okay" kind of okay...

475
00:17:21,472 --> 00:17:23,306
MAX CHANGMIN: I'm asking if you're scared or not.

476
00:17:24,224 --> 00:17:25,040
CHARLIE: A bit scared.

477
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,336
- MAX CHANGMIN: Scared?
- CHARLIE: Yes.

478
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:26,976
MAX CHANGMIN: What about JAEWON?

479
00:17:26,976 --> 00:17:27,616
JAEWON: I'm scared too.

480
00:17:28,608 --> 00:17:30,464
MAX CHANGMIN: Then, what's okay?

481
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,383
((Not) okay)
MAX CHANGMIN: The scariest.

482
00:17:32,896 --> 00:17:35,296
(Next question)
MAX CHANGMIN: Romance or action movie?

483
00:17:35,712 --> 00:17:36,461
HARUTA: Action movie for me.

484
00:17:37,792 --> 00:17:39,392
MAX CHANGMIN: You don't really like
melodramas that much, do you?

485
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:39,840
HARUTA: Yes.

486
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:40,776
HAMIN: Huh?

487
00:17:42,304 --> 00:17:43,884
HAMIN: You don't like melodramas?

488
00:17:44,064 --> 00:17:44,832
HAMIN: (same-age) This guy...

489
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,176
HAMIN: When I suggested watching an action movie,

490
00:17:46,353 --> 00:17:47,372
HAMIN: he has never watched it with me.

491
00:17:48,192 --> 00:17:49,536
DANIEL: Is it just because it's you?

492
00:17:49,536 --> 00:17:50,400
HAMIN: No, no, no!

493
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:54,592
HAMIN: Never watched it, always
watching melodrama anime or

494
00:17:54,592 --> 00:17:55,840
HAMIN: dramas.

495
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:59,830
JAEWON: HARUTA is really sensitive,
always listening to Korean ballads.

496
00:18:00,576 --> 00:18:02,016
(Imitating HARUTA singing)

497
00:18:02,016 --> 00:18:04,384
(Mirror therapy)

498
00:18:04,384 --> 00:18:06,845
DANIEL: That's it! Yeah!

499
00:18:06,845 --> 00:18:07,852
(Classmates helping with meta-cognition)

500
00:18:08,224 --> 00:18:08,945
(HAMIN's test of typical performance)
MAX CHANGMIN: Come on.

501
00:18:09,408 --> 00:18:12,104
(How does it feel to enter Hogwarts?)
MAX CHANGMIN: How does it feel to enroll in Hogwarts?

502
00:18:12,862 --> 00:18:13,920
HAMIN: Don't really respond to those kinds of jokes.

503
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,256
(Cutting in without a signal)
JAEWON: Yes, that's right, I always use examples like...

504
00:18:17,225 --> 00:18:18,080
(Cut-ins are welcome)
MAX CHANGMIN: Go ahead.

505
00:18:18,272 --> 00:18:18,720
JAEWON: I'm just...

506
00:18:18,816 --> 00:18:20,096
DANIEL: There's a lot you want to say.

507
00:18:21,472 --> 00:18:23,072
MAX CHANGMIN: JAEWON's got a lot built up.

508
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:26,624
MAX CHANGMIN: You went to karaoke
with your tone-deaf friend,

509
00:18:26,624 --> 00:18:28,512
MAX CHANGMIN: and after their
passionate singing, they asked proudly,

510
00:18:28,512 --> 00:18:29,719
(Haha...)
MAX CHANGMIN: "did I do well?"

511
00:18:30,144 --> 00:18:31,520
MAX CHANGMIN: How do you react at this moment?

512
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,184
MAX CHANGMIN: (Option 1) I think
you have a really nice tone.

513
00:18:33,184 --> 00:18:34,716
MAX CHANGMIN: Trying to compliment somehow.

514
00:18:35,008 --> 00:18:37,024
MAX CHANGMIN: Option 2, give an honest assessment.

515
00:18:37,248 --> 00:18:38,156
HAMIN: I choose option 1.

516
00:18:38,368 --> 00:18:39,030
JAEWON: Huh?

517
00:18:39,264 --> 00:18:40,288
(Compliments?)

518
00:18:40,288 --> 00:18:41,088
TRAINEE: Ah, this is true.

519
00:18:41,088 --> 00:18:42,232
HARUTA: No, no, no, no.

520
00:18:42,232 --> 00:18:43,808
(Testimonies pouring from all directions)
- DANIEL: Definitely not. - HARUTA: No, no.

521
00:18:43,823 --> 00:18:44,672
HAMIN: Ah, because

522
00:18:44,672 --> 00:18:46,016
HAMIN: friends here

523
00:18:46,263 --> 00:18:48,320
HAMIN: want honest assessments too.

524
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:50,016
(Who held a grudge?)
MAX CHANGMIN: Because they're precious friends to you?

525
00:18:50,016 --> 00:18:50,891
HARUTA: No, no, no, no, no.

526
00:18:51,936 --> 00:18:53,024
(Unfair)
HAMIN: No, seriously.

527
00:18:53,408 --> 00:18:54,112
(Excitement)

528
00:18:54,112 --> 00:18:54,942
MAX CHANGMIN: Why?

529
00:18:54,942 --> 00:18:57,472
JAEWON: When we were practicing hard,
he suddenly came in...

530
00:18:57,472 --> 00:18:59,968
(JAEWON mimicking HAMIN's mimicking
of JAEWON's practice)

531
00:18:59,968 --> 00:19:01,408
JAEWON: Mimicking like this suddenly...

532
00:19:01,408 --> 00:19:02,784
HAMIN: Ah, this is teasing.

533
00:19:02,784 --> 00:19:05,438
(Gathering opinions)
MAX CHANGMIN: Basically you start by mocking.

534
00:19:05,438 --> 00:19:06,848
(Dizzy...)

535
00:19:06,848 --> 00:19:07,424
HAMIN: That's not true.

536
00:19:07,424 --> 00:19:08,704
(Final conclusion)
DANIEL: You're almost like a critic.

537
00:19:09,216 --> 00:19:10,432
(Freaking out)

538
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,544
HAMIN: Ah, this is unfair for me too really.

539
00:19:13,664 --> 00:19:14,848
(Why unfair?)
- DANIEL: Why? - HAMIN: It's really not.

540
00:19:14,848 --> 00:19:15,328
DANIEL: Isn't it true?

541
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,376
(Ask the critic)
MAX CHANGMIN: Delivery vs. homemade meals.

542
00:19:17,376 --> 00:19:18,368
DANIEL: Isn't it homemade meals?

543
00:19:18,368 --> 00:19:21,952
DANIEL: Even when we're eating delivery food,
you're like 'Ah, homemade meals are tastier.'

544
00:19:22,752 --> 00:19:24,928
MAX CHANGMIN: You evaluate even while eating?

545
00:19:24,928 --> 00:19:26,400
(Stop teasing)
DANIEL: Ah this is slightly exaggerating, but

546
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:28,064
DANIEL: he always misses homemade meals.

547
00:19:28,064 --> 00:19:30,656
HAMIN: That's right. Yes,
actually I'm good with any meal if it has rice.

548
00:19:31,136 --> 00:19:33,089
HAMIN: It's kind of... for me...

549
00:19:33,802 --> 00:19:35,008
HAMIN: For me... it's kind of...

550
00:19:38,144 --> 00:19:39,616
(Isn't it over yet?)

551
00:19:39,616 --> 00:19:41,136
- DANIEL: I was listening (not...).
- HAMIN: For me...

552
00:19:41,344 --> 00:19:44,000
(Critic speaking firmly)
HAMIN: This question is a bit meaningless to me.

553
00:19:44,154 --> 00:19:46,144
(Summarized)
MAX CHANGMIN: Is rice all it takes?

554
00:19:46,848 --> 00:19:47,968
(In the 90s A.U.I class...)
TRAINEE: Did you eat a lot?

555
00:19:47,968 --> 00:19:49,664
TRAINEE: I ate three today.

556
00:19:50,048 --> 00:19:51,904
(Student Record Day)

557
00:19:51,904 --> 00:19:54,080
(Measuring body stats)

558
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,896
(This record includes all sorts of false facts)

559
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:59,827
(Scale from those days)
HYUNJUN: It was hard to weigh in the old days.

560
00:20:00,672 --> 00:20:01,916
NICHOLAS: Ah!

561
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:03,546
(Mastering scale tricks)
TRAINEE: If you do it like this...

562
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,088
TRAINEE: Just let it be.

563
00:20:05,088 --> 00:20:08,448
HYUNJUN: It's better in the old days!
You could set your own weight!

564
00:20:08,448 --> 00:20:09,466
(Using a trick)
TRAINEE: Seriously...

565
00:20:10,048 --> 00:20:11,392
TRAINEE: 25kg.

566
00:20:11,392 --> 00:20:12,224
(Devil's whisper)
KASSHO: Measure it properly!

567
00:20:12,224 --> 00:20:12,544
TRAINEE: Ah.

568
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:13,344
HAMIN: Really, for real?

569
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:14,752
- KASSHO: For real.
- HAMIN: I'll give it a try.

570
00:20:15,424 --> 00:20:16,127
HAMIN: Huh? No way!

571
00:20:16,576 --> 00:20:17,632
(Collapsed without resistance)
TRAINEE: No way.

572
00:20:18,272 --> 00:20:18,949
(JUSTIN)
TRAINEE: Whoa, what's this?

573
00:20:19,168 --> 00:20:19,808
(Lift up)

574
00:20:19,808 --> 00:20:21,650
(Gently)
HAMIN: Oh, gosh!

575
00:20:22,124 --> 00:20:24,192
(WOOLIN's weight 1kg)
TRAINEE: Okay, 1kg.

576
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:27,008
KACHIN: What's your goal?

577
00:20:27,008 --> 00:20:28,559
HANBI: My goal?

578
00:20:28,559 --> 00:20:28,832
KACHIN: Yes.

579
00:20:28,832 --> 00:20:29,536
(My goal 60kg)
HANBI: 60kg.

580
00:20:29,536 --> 00:20:30,376
TRAINEE: 60kg?

581
00:20:31,264 --> 00:20:32,925
(A step towards 60kg)

582
00:20:32,925 --> 00:20:34,432
TRAINEE: Oh, what?

583
00:20:34,432 --> 00:20:35,360
(Goal achieved)
TRAINEE: Oh 60, exactly!

584
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,408
(Indeed, books are nourishment
for the mind (literally))

585
00:20:37,408 --> 00:20:38,720
HANBI: Exactly 60.

586
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,920
(KACHIN's target weight is 64kg)
KACHIN: My goal is 64, here we go.

587
00:20:42,272 --> 00:20:43,732
(Boldly on the scale)

588
00:20:44,087 --> 00:20:45,762
(Results below expectations)
TRAINEE: Just a little more.

589
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:46,855
(Nourishing the soul, while gaining weight)
KACHIN: Just a little more.

590
00:20:48,512 --> 00:20:50,100
(Still a bit lacking...)

591
00:20:50,342 --> 00:20:52,855
(This time, with a thick book)

592
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:53,440
(Curious)

593
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,368
(2kg short...)

594
00:20:54,368 --> 00:20:55,424
TRAINEE: Not yet, not yet...

595
00:20:55,872 --> 00:20:57,728
(My right foot just helps)

596
00:20:57,792 --> 00:20:59,941
(+HANBI)

597
00:21:00,544 --> 00:21:01,248
(Finally achieved 65kg)
TRAINEE: Okay!

598
00:21:01,248 --> 00:21:02,560
- TRAINEE: 65!
- TRAINEE: Okay!

599
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,863
KACHIN: Okay

600
00:21:03,968 --> 00:21:04,762
(+Desk)(+Books)
CHARLIE: More...

601
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,144
(+DANIEL)
TRAINEE: Ask for more.

602
00:21:06,144 --> 00:21:06,976
(Taking it up a notch, WONHA~JANNI class)
DANIEL: Like this.

603
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,544
DANIEL: 100kg.

604
00:21:08,544 --> 00:21:09,900
- CHARLIE: 100kg!
- DANIEL: 100kg!

605
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:10,848
(CHARLIE's weight is 100kg)
- TRAINEE: 100kg! - TRAINEE: 100kg!

606
00:21:10,848 --> 00:21:11,872
TRAINEE: Okay, nice!

607
00:21:12,064 --> 00:21:13,024
TRAINEE: 90.

608
00:21:13,024 --> 00:21:13,900
(HAMIN's measurement equipment: CHARLIE)
TRAINEE: 90.

609
00:21:15,146 --> 00:21:16,583
(Entering with a princess carry)

610
00:21:16,583 --> 00:21:17,811
HAMIN: Check.

611
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,933
(HAMIN's weight: 103kg)
HAMIN: 103kg.

612
00:21:22,766 --> 00:21:24,066
JAEWON: One leg is 30kg?

613
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:26,566
(One leg comparable to a sack of rice)

614
00:21:27,766 --> 00:21:29,069
JAEWON: No, it's already like this.

615
00:21:29,069 --> 00:21:30,272
(Whining)
JAEWON: Seriously.

616
00:21:30,272 --> 00:21:31,008
(Sorry)

617
00:21:31,666 --> 00:21:33,533
(Finally, both legs on the scale)

618
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:35,072
(35kg, not much difference from one leg)

619
00:21:35,072 --> 00:21:36,300
JAEWON: 35kg.

620
00:21:37,312 --> 00:21:38,528
HAMIN: Huh?

621
00:21:39,199 --> 00:21:40,533
JAEWON: 35kg.

622
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:41,999
JAEWON: I'm the lightest here.

623
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:43,299
HYUNJUN: Hey, the 90s were great.

624
00:21:43,299 --> 00:21:44,333
HYUNJUN: You can adjust it.

625
00:21:44,704 --> 00:21:45,952
JUSTIN: Then we can adjust the height too.

626
00:21:46,432 --> 00:21:47,488
(Application skills)

627
00:21:48,128 --> 00:21:50,112
(Happy)

628
00:21:50,688 --> 00:21:52,864
(Analog height measurement from those days)

629
00:21:53,088 --> 00:21:53,966
KASSHO: Are you ready?

630
00:21:53,966 --> 00:21:54,933
NICHOLAS: Oh, it worked!

631
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:56,448
(Carrying KASSHO securely)
TRAINEE: Okay!

632
00:21:56,605 --> 00:21:57,472
TRAINEE: The height...

633
00:21:57,472 --> 00:21:58,240
(Uh-huh)
TRAINEE: Is it done?

634
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,424
HYUNJUN: It's unmeasurable.

635
00:21:59,552 --> 00:22:00,992
(Uh-huh)
TRAINEE: 180...

636
00:22:00,992 --> 00:22:02,200
(Building friendship with friends)
HYUNJUN: Isn't this it?

637
00:22:02,976 --> 00:22:03,648
(Uh-huh)

638
00:22:03,648 --> 00:22:05,266
- JUSTIN: Hurry up.
- TRAINEE: 185.

639
00:22:05,266 --> 00:22:07,300
(Grown to 185.7cm through friendship)
TRAINEE: 185.7 cm.

640
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:08,633
(As soon as the height was checked)
TRAINEE: 185.7 cm.

641
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,100
(Come down)
TRAINEE: It's big.

642
00:22:10,166 --> 00:22:12,200
JUSTIN: Last time I measured,

643
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:14,733
(Not foot size)
JUSTIN: I was around 240.

644
00:22:14,944 --> 00:22:15,648
(Mm)

645
00:22:16,192 --> 00:22:16,992
(Helper 1)
JUSTIN: I'm going.

646
00:22:17,408 --> 00:22:18,688
(Helper 2)

647
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,610
JUSTIN: How...

648
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:21,408
JUSTIN: How do I lift my hips?

649
00:22:21,632 --> 00:22:22,656
JUSTIN: How do I lift my hips?

650
00:22:22,656 --> 00:22:23,488
(A hip that comes out alone)

651
00:22:23,904 --> 00:22:25,312
KASSHO: You gotta lift it.

652
00:22:25,866 --> 00:22:28,100
(Me, my hips?)
HYUNJUN: Your hips? Like this?

653
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,466
HYUNJUN: Like this?

654
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:32,448
(With help from three people, taking on the challenge)

655
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,472
JUSTIN: Move further back.

656
00:22:33,664 --> 00:22:34,368
TRAINEE: Let's go with 50.

657
00:22:34,533 --> 00:22:35,833
TRAINEE: There's no 250.

658
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,299
(240cm, a sharp drop to 209cm since last measurement)
TRAINEE: 209 cm.

659
00:22:38,466 --> 00:22:39,999
HANBI: It's worth sacrificing some for height.

660
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:40,992
(Thud)

661
00:22:41,266 --> 00:22:42,560
(Bumping the head against the measurement device)

662
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:43,442
SADAHARU: That must've hurt.

663
00:22:44,096 --> 00:22:44,566
SONGHA: One more time.

664
00:22:44,566 --> 00:22:45,699
(2nd try)

665
00:22:45,699 --> 00:22:46,944
(3rd try)

666
00:22:46,944 --> 00:22:48,160
(4th try)
SONGHA: A bit more.

667
00:22:48,557 --> 00:22:49,760
(5th try)
SONGHA: A bit more

668
00:22:50,199 --> 00:22:51,488
(6th try)
SONGHA: A bit more, let's hit 2 meters.

669
00:22:51,872 --> 00:22:52,896
(7th try) (The harsh instructor)
SONGHA: A bit more!

670
00:22:53,466 --> 00:22:55,166
(8th try)
SONGHA: It's done, it's done.

671
00:22:56,064 --> 00:22:57,056
(HANBI's height: 202cm, with impact)
TRAINEE: 202 cm.

672
00:22:57,566 --> 00:22:58,599
(Next, KACHIN's turn)

673
00:23:01,024 --> 00:23:02,496
(Pulling deftly)

674
00:23:03,299 --> 00:23:05,120
(What's going on?)
KACHIN: Wow, what is this?

675
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:06,496
TRAINEE: KACHIN is awesome!

676
00:23:06,624 --> 00:23:08,099
(KACHIN's height: 210cm)
TRAINEE: 210 cm.

677
00:23:10,299 --> 00:23:11,999
(Class '00, lastly SADAHARU)
SADAHARU: 5, 6, 7, 8.

678
00:23:12,384 --> 00:23:13,472
(It hurts)

679
00:23:14,496 --> 00:23:15,776
(Shock)
SADAHARU: Oh!

680
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:17,568
(Growing pain)
SADAHARU: It hurts!

681
00:23:17,632 --> 00:23:18,560
TRAINEE: Are you okay?

682
00:23:19,066 --> 00:23:20,999
(SADAHARU's height: 139.3cm)
TRAINEE: 8.3...

683
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:23,499
SADAHARU: It hurt.

684
00:23:23,646 --> 00:23:24,133
TRAINEE: I'm going.

685
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:25,866
(Re-measurement)
TRAINEE: Okay.

686
00:23:26,368 --> 00:23:27,264
SADAHARU: It hurts.

687
00:23:27,424 --> 00:23:28,448
TRAINEE: Just right.

688
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,536
TATA: 9...

689
00:23:29,894 --> 00:23:30,466
SADAHARU: 190.9 cm.

690
00:23:30,466 --> 00:23:31,666
(Quite satisfying result)
TRAINEE: 190.9 cm.

691
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:32,608
TRAINEE: Please...

692
00:23:32,608 --> 00:23:34,112
(Getting ready...)

693
00:23:34,592 --> 00:23:36,480
(Tension...)

694
00:23:36,866 --> 00:23:37,984
JAEWON: Why are you so nervous?

695
00:23:38,144 --> 00:23:39,168
(Feeling guilty)

